					<h2><a name="news">Managing NEWS articles</a></h2>
					
					<p>News articles appear on the Home page as well as the News page.  The Home page shows the 2 most recently-created articles, and the text of each article is truncated for brevity.</p>
					<p>To create a new News article that will appear on both the News page as well as the Home page:</p>
					<ol>
						<li>Log into the admin area of the website at <a href="http://john1512ministries.org/refinery/" target="_blank">http://john1512ministries.org/refinery/</a></li>
						<li>Click the News tab.  Notice that a list of existing news articles will appear.  (NOTE: The right side of the list displays icons that allow you to Delete, Edit, and View existing news articles.)</li>
						<li>Click 'Create News Item' on the right-hand side of the screen.</li>
						<li>Enter the Title of the article, and supply a publish date.</li>
						<li>Next, you need to supply the body of the article itself.  You may copy and paste from your favorite text editor directly into the Content area, or you can type the article directly into the Content area from scratch.  Note that if you choose to type from scratch, you should use a web browser like Firefox that has automatic spell check enabled so that you're alerted as you type of any spelling mistakes.</li>
						<li>IMPORTANT: After you finish entering your news article, click but Save button in the lower left.  Note that you may still return to the article to edit it, or you may delete the article altogether.</li>
					</ol> 
				</div>
				
				<div class="newsStory">
					<h2><a name="stories">Managing STORIES</a></h2>
					
					<p>To create a new Story that will appear in the "STORIES" area of the website:</p>
					<ol>
						<li>Log into the admin area of the website at <a href="http://john1512ministries.org/refinery/" target="_blank">http://john1512ministries.org/refinery/</a></li>
						<li>Click the Blog tab.  Notice that a list of existing blog posts will appear.  (NOTE: The right side of the list displays icons that allow you to Delete, Edit, and View existing blog posts.)</li>
						<li>Click 'Create new post' on the right-hand side of the screen.</li>
						<li>Enter the Title of the post in the upper text field, and the text of the post in the 'Body' field.  In the 'Body' text field, you may copy and paste from your favorite text editor directly, or you can type text directly into the field from scratch.  Note that if you choose to type from scratch, you should use a web browser like Firefox that has automatic spell check enabled so that you're alerted as you type of any spelling mistakes.</li>
						<li>IMPORTANT: After you finish entering your blog post, click but Save button in the lower left.  Note that you may still return to the post to edit it, or you may delete the post altogether.</li>
					</ol> 
				</div>
				
