					<h2><a name="inquiries">Managing INQUIRIES</a></h2>
					
					<p>When a user clicks the 'Contact' link in the main navigation, completes the form and clicks the 'Send message' button, an email is sent to John 15:12, and the message is recorded in the admin area of the website.  In addition, the user who completed the form will receive a confirmation email thanking them for the inquiry.</p>
					<p>Inside the admin area, the Inquiries tab displays a listing of all submissions made via the Contact form.  The small icons repeated with each item in the list allow you to: mark an item as spam, read the full text of the inquiry, and delete the inquiry (the deletion is permanent).
					The buttons on the far right are 'Spam' (view any messages marked as spam), 'Update who gets notified' (update the email address used when a user sends you a message via the 'Contact' link on the site) and 'Edit confirmation email' (allows you to customize the Subject and Body text of the confirmation email received by users who copmlete the Contact form).
				</div>
				
